Class JsonFactory, JsonParser createJsonParser(InputStream, Charset)

Returns a new instance of a low-level JSON parser for the given input stream.

Upgrade warning: Prior to version 1.11 this method would not accept {@code null} for the charset parameter. Since 1.11 {@code null} is allowed and will force the underlying parser to pick/detect the charset for the stream.

@param in input stream @param charset non-null charset in which the input stream is encoded encoded or {@code null} to let the parser detect the charset @return new instance of a low-level JSON parser @since 1.10
Class JsonGenerator

Abstract low-level JSON serializer.

Implementation has no fields and therefore thread-safe, but sub-classes are not necessarily thread-safe.

Backwards incompatibility warning: 1.9 introduced .writeNumber(UnsignedInteger) and .writeNumber(UnsignedLong) to this abstract class. @since 1.3 @author Yaniv Inbar
Class JsonParser

Abstract low-level JSON parser.

Implementation has no fields and therefore thread-safe, but sub-classes are not necessarily thread-safe.

Backwards incompatibility warning: 1.9 introduced .getUnsignedIntegerValue and .getUnsignedLongValue to this abstract class. @since 1.3 @author Yaniv Inbar
Class JsonParser, String skipToKey(Set<String>)

Skips the values of all keys in the current object until it finds one of the given keys.

Before this method is called, the parser must either point to the start or end of a JSON object or to a field name. After this method ends, the current token will either be the JsonToken.END_OBJECT of the current object if no matching key is found, or the value ofvalue of the key that was found.

@param keysToFind set of keys to look for @return name of the first matching key found or {@code null} if no match was found @since 1.10
